---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Best Shopify Email Apps for Email and SMS in 2026';
const description = 'Compare Shopify email apps for coordinated email and SMS by consent, channel orchestration, suppression, pricing context, sources, and tradeoffs.';
const apps = [['Klaviyo','Behavioral email and SMS journeys','Detailed events and cross-channel controls','Channel costs and consent governance need attention','https://www.klaviyo.com/features/segmentation'],['Omnisend','Retail teams wanting accessible email/SMS workflows','Campaign and automation coordination','Frequency and SMS economics require discipline','https://www.omnisend.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['Sequenzy','Email-first teams with occasional SMS needs','Focused email sequence operations','May not replace a full SMS stack','https://sequenzy.io/'],['Brevo','Email, transactional, and SMS coverage','Broad messaging toolkit','More manual commerce orchestration','https://www.brevo.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['Shopify Email','Email foundations before adding SMS','Native campaign setup','Not a complete multichannel system','https://www.shopify.com/email-marketing']];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}><main class="container page-stack"><p class="eyebrow">Shopify email apps</p><h1>{title}</h1><p class="lede">Email and SMS work best as complementary channels. Email can carry education and detail; SMS can handle genuinely time-sensitive reminders. The platform should make consent, suppression, and channel priority explicit.</p><p>We prioritize cross-channel orchestration, frequency caps, opt-out behavior, and total-cost visibility. Confirm current vendor pricing and regional messaging rules from official sources before activating SMS.</p><h2>Shortlist</h2><table><thead><tr><th>App</th><th>Best fit</th><th>First journey</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{apps.map(a=><tr><td>{a[0]}</td><td>{a[1]}</td><td>{a[0]==='Klaviyo'?'Email/SMS suppression':a[0]==='Omnisend'?'Launch coordination':a[0]==='Sequenzy'?'Email-first lifecycle':a[0]==='Brevo'?'Transactional plus SMS':'Email foundation'}</td><td>{a[3]}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table>{apps.map(a=><section><h2>{a[0]} for email and SMS</h2><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {a[1]}. {a[0]} is useful when the store can say why each channel is appropriate and when the other channel should remain quiet. Never assume email consent automatically covers SMS, or use an urgent channel for routine content.</p><p><strong>Why it stands out:</strong> {a[2]}. Start with one journey and define the channel decision before writing creative. Measure incremental orders, opt-outs, complaints, and cost per qualified action together instead of treating every SMS click as extra revenue.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Pros</th><td>{a[2]}; supports a coordinated-channel test; can use Shopify events.</td></tr><tr><th>Cons</th><td>{a[3]}; SMS fees and consent requirements can change the economics.</td></tr><tr><th>Pricing context</th><td>Verify official contacts, sends, seats, SMS fees, and regional compliance terms.</td></tr><tr><th>Source</th><td><a href={a[4]} rel="nofollow">Official product information</a></td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}<h2>Decision guide</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Priority</th><th>Start with</th><th>Reason</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Deep cross-channel behavior</td><td>Klaviyo</td><td>Flexible event and suppression controls.</td></tr><tr><td>Accessible retail orchestration</td><td>Omnisend</td><td>Fast email/SMS campaign setup.</td></tr><tr><td>Email-first foundations</td><td>Sequenzy</td><td>Focused lifecycle operations.</td></tr></tbody></table><p>See the <a href="/shopify-email">Shopify email overview</a>, <a href="/alternatives">alternatives library</a>, and <a href="/guides/consent-compliance">consent guide</a>.</p></main></BaseLayout>
